snippet.textDisplay:
Epidemics happen every couple of years. Check the facts online. Only 4 out of 62 epidemics in 21st century started in China. Don’t blame Chinese. I hope your government is ready for the next epidemic.
In 2009, H1N1 started in Mexico and then spread to US. The virus had been present for months before it was officially called an "epidemic". More than 200,000 people died of it. In 2013, Ebola outbroke in West Africa. More than 11,000 people died of it.
Chinese government locked down 65 million people in 18 cities to prevent the spread of the virus in the world. Chinese people make 3 billion (yes, 3 billion) travels during the Chinese New Year season (about 40 days) and 120 million international travels each year. Domestic travels declined 80% after the lockdown and nearly all recent international travels had been cancelled. The whole country is literally at a halt. Be thankful that you are still fine.
Chinese people have been eating wild animals for thousands of years. So do people in Vietnam, South Korea, North Korea, Thailand and many other countries in Asia. Chinese eating habit is not the reason why the virus started in China. Don’t blame Chinese for our eating habits. As for bat soup, I must claim that nobody eats bats. People like to watch weird videos. That’s why you saw the video of girls eating bats. Find out for yourselve about bat soup: https://user.guancha.cn/main/content?id=230421. Nobody really eats bats. If you don't read Chinese, use google translate.
